      </prefercite>
      <custodhist id="aspace_28453415317289ee84a808d8f0b38776">
         <head>Custodial History</head>
         <p>Accession 2012-A-075 transferred from Media Services, 2010.</p>  
      </custodhist>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_5443a28eff21912edaea87a6025d7c0a">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
         <p>Original audiovisual materials, as well as preservation and duplicating masters, may not be played. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist must pay for a use copy, which is retained by the repository. Researchers wishing to obtain an additional copy for their personal use should consult Copying Services information on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <arrangement id="aspace_1777a1d515862b3cdd926c110ee06127">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by topic and additional material.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_985c812c76af966ecbdb1428ef5425b4">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Old Art Gallery (Old Wing) at Yale was completed in 1928. A bridge over High Street, connecting Street Hall to the Art Gallery, was constructed at the same time. The New Art Gallery (New Wing) adjoins the Old Wing on the west side. The New Wing was completed in 1953.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_5d30af49fc64ae8e39ff018ddb543a42">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The materials consist of photographs, drawings and one 16mm film documenting the two stages of construction of the Yale University Art Gallery (Gallery of Fine Arts).</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <odd id="aspace_0b784a0b7d57195f616ed4b0e31439f6">
         <head>General</head>
         <p>Formerly titled: Yale University Art Gallery Photographs.  Title revised 3/29/2012.</p>  
      </odd>
